If you started vaccination last year or earlier, you will have to pay for the following vaccinations yourself.
The first dose of the vaccine should be administered between the 3rd and 5th month of the child.
Last year, a quarter of families voluntarily vaccinated their children against pneumococcal disease.
However, the parents paid 1,600 crowns or more for a dose.
Vaccination of the youngest requires four doses.
Specialists estimate that every year health insurance spends 300 to 450,000 crowns in vaccine doses.
However, they save on the medical care that unvaccinated children would need.
So far, the state has spent about 500,000 crowns a year on all children's vaccinations.
The refunded vaccination was introduced with the "Janota package".
Pneumococcals are the cause of inflammation of the middle ear but also of serious infections including meningitis and blood poisoning.
According to investigations in hospitals, there are up to 28 deaths of children under the age of 10 caused by pneumococcal infections.
Aside from the Czech Republic, about 40 other countries have introduced the refunded vaccination.
Will vaccination be compulsory?
There are warnings about a possible vaccination obligation in the future.
Starting in January, it must be settled by insurance and optional.
For example, the president of the Nahlas Rudolf Kalovsk<0xC3><0xBD> association indicated that compulsory vaccination would be more positive.
Its association has long promoted the vaccination against pneumococcal diseases.
At an international conference in which our association participated, the specialists were not really satisfied with the fact that we have an optional vaccination.
