It sets out the guidelines for a possible agreement in which industrial nations would collectively reduce their emissions in 2020 from 25 to 45 per cent compared to 1990 levels, while major developing countries would, during the same period, reduce theirs from 15 to 30 per cent.
Together, countries would reduce emissions by 50-95 percent by 2050.
