The CNMV authorizes the OPA of exclusion of Paternina presented by Inversora Mer
The National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) approved yesterday the exclusion OPA presented by Inversora Mer on Federico Paternina on October 9.
The supervisory body explained that it was authorizing this operation because it understood that its terms were in line with current standards and that it considered the content of the explanatory leaflet submitted “sufficient” following the amendments applied on December 2.
The CNMV stated that the offer concerns the acquisition of 550 008 shares of Federico Paternina at a price of EUR 7.65 per share, which represents 8.95 % of the share capital, consisting of 6,142,786 shares admitted to trading on the Madrid and Bilbao stock exchanges.
He further explained that 5 592 778 million shares had been fixed, and that they could in no way be transferred before the finalization of the tender, of which he indicated that the price had been fixed by Federico Paternina, in accordance with the provisions of the standards in force.
New Tools for Cars Expertise
In these days of bad weather and accidents, car garages are not the only winners.
Every day, thousands of cars that have suffered a crash are taken back to a garage, where an expert has to assess the damage suffered and the cost of repair.
Each sinking is different, and calculating the cost of parts and labor time can be a long and complex job.
Calculating manually the cost of a repair between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including the parts and the workmanship can take two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the assistance of the latest computer tools, it would be a matter of minutes.
This is why almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service providers and solutions for accident assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting information provided by manufacturers, then processing it and offering it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, from the North American group Solera, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other companies competing in the field of assessment tools and industry information development are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with data provided by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Commercial Director of Audatex, the company in Spain with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is constantly increasing, so that over the past five years, more versions, variants and motors have been launched than in the previous fifteen years.
When a new car comes on the market, these companies get to work.
This is a very hard job, because you have to catalog each of the thousand parts of the vehicle and register its price.
In addition, a “smart” graphic image of each model is created, on which the different parts of a passenger car can be clicked.
If it is a massively sold model, the work can be ready in a week if the process progresses very quickly.
If it is a low-selling car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models, they have information about, for example, Porsche, but not Ferrari or Lamborghini.
In the case of vehicles in circulation, the figure exceeds 99%.
To carry out the work of documentation and database development, Audatex has eight centers spread around the world (in Spain, France, Germany, the United States, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in certain brands.
The National Headquarters is located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audatex invests $90 million each year to develop these databases.
Every month, 2.5 million data is recorded, and customers receive updates every two days.
The development of this huge flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and to offer different products.
The most common application concerns repair and maintenance, but depending on the country, there are also tools for the management of breakage parts or to calculate the venal or residual value of a car.
The only company that has a guide that informs about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer it in our country, but it does in the United States.
In view of the products offered by Audatex, it is easy to get an idea of the type of support it can provide to professionals in the sector.
This company offers ten different tools, the flagship product being AudaPlus, the standard solution for accident assessment, intended for experts.
These include cars, motorcycles, light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it takes into account the estimated repair times by the manufacturer or paint scales.
This tool is purchased depending on its use, for each estimate.
The highest cost is 5.75 euros, for customers who use it little, a maximum of ten times a month.
Then, each insurance company, which carries out thousands of tests, negotiates its price with Audatex.
Other products, such as AudaVIN, allow the total identification of a vehicle and the equipment with which it came out of the assembly line, only thanks to its chassis number.
AudaGlass focuses on vehicle lenses, and AudaSubastas is a server open to the professional sector on the Internet that allows bidding on vehicles declared wrecked.
Its statistics service is very useful for identifying trends, performing geo-demographic analyses or knowing the common problems by brand or model.
It is possible to study, for example, how many models of a certain brand went to the garage for a breakdown or how many suffered serious accidents for a given period.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of tools.
It markets, among other things, Gt Estimate, which is also intended for experts and provides digital images, as well as access to the official parts, prices and time of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the Einsa Group, founded in 1971, as a provider of services and solutions for accident assessment, breakdown or car maintenance.
The GT Evaluation Guide is a historical reference product on the market.
The company works with 24,000 users in garages, 3,100 experts and 53 insurance companies.
Its turnover has increased at a rate of 20% per year over the past three years, and it made a turnover of <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>10.8 million in 2008.
At the beginning of last year, she undertook her internationalization process, with the establishment of an office in Paris.
Audatex was born in Germany in 1966 and settled in Spain in 1979.
According to the company's sources, 62% of its turnover is generated in Europe and the rest of the world, and the remaining 38% in North and South America. It works with 900 insurance companies and 33,000 garages, of which 3,000 are located in Spain.
Solera Group’s global turnover (Audatex, Sidexa, Informex ABZ, Hollander and IMS) will be $557 million, 3.3% more than in 2008.
In our country, the company will receive 19.1 million euros, which is 7.2% more than last year.
In 2005, the Solera Group was listed on a $1 billion stock exchange, today its shares are valued at a total of $2,400 million.
Since 2007, it has been on the New York Stock Exchange and is part of the Standard & Poor's benchmark index.
Internet Auctions for Accidented Cars
Last October, the Solera Group purchased Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of cars, motorcycles and specialty vehicles damaged.
The transaction involved a cost of <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could expand to the remaining 15% next year.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of accessing an immense international market.
This estimation and sales service is exclusively aimed at professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, garages, brokers and professional sellers who must be registered before starting operations.
This platform was established in 1996 in Germany and manages more than 650,000 operations across Europe, including 500,000 in Germany.
Among its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1500 sellers and 4000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3,000 ads per day and in the Spanish market, 100 new ads are published every day.
According to Spanish law, a car whose chassis number has been removed can no longer circulate, but on the other hand, some parts that are not damaged can be used as spare parts.
Collectible cars can be re-registered, although they have been removed, after complex steps.
Garage quotation in four stages
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user gets a quote in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the spare part, create a quote and generate it.
Ease of use is an essential part of these systems, especially to convince older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are receptive to the use of new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 passenger vehicles, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it, a computer and an Internet connection are required.
Once the model to be repaired has been identified by its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and the required part is selected.
The user can include variables such as labor price, increases or reductions, then he can print the quote to hand it over to the customer.
AudaTaller is not an estimation tool like AudaPlus, but a reference catalog.
The main difference between these two systems is that the one intended for garages does not include estimated labor times.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which can be subject to a credit.
Currently, the company Audatex is working to ensure that these images are in three dimensions.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with a very good eye, since it will, for example, allow you to select a door and rotate it to see the inner face.
